Key Match Events: David Fry high-flied Alomar as he rounded first base, his momentum-shifting, series-saving, visitors-dugout-quaking home run — the first go-ahead, pinch hit blast in franchise history — having disappeared into the Detroit Tigers’ bullpen.
Post-Match Reflections: 'A big reason why we’re here right now,' Hedges said, 'is because of David Fry.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Fry delivered a pinch-hit home run in the seventh inning to go ahead in the series.
Fry also squeezed in a run with a bunt in the ninth inning.
Fry predicted José Ramírez’s home run in a dugout conversation with Hedges before Ramírez deposited a pitch into the left-field seats.
